# coding-aegis

Browse, install, and manage governance packages for coding agents.

## Catalog

Packages are organized by tier:

| Tier | Purpose | Install behavior |
|------|---------|------------------|
| **required** | Non-negotiable governance | Auto-installed |
| **best-practices** | Recommended defaults | Opt-out with justification |
| **optional** | Available on demand | Opt-in |
| **goodies** | Community and experimental | Opt-in |

The catalog lives at `pkgs/` in the coding-aegis repository. Each package contains a `pkg.yaml` manifest describing its artifacts (skills, agents, rules, MCP configs).

## Package Format

Every package has a `pkg.yaml`:

```yaml
name: my-package
version: 0.1.0
description: What this package provides
author: team-name
artifacts:
  - type: rule          # rule | skill | agent | mcp
    path: rules/my-rule.mdc
```

## Installation

Packages install artifacts to tool-native locations:

| Artifact | Claude Code | Cursor | Windsurf | Copilot |
|----------|-------------|--------|----------|---------|
| skill | `.claude/skills/{name}/` | `.cursor/skills/{name}/` | `.agents/skills/{name}/` | — |
| agent | `.claude/agents/` | — | — | — |
| rule | `.claude/rules/` | `.cursor/rules/` | `.windsurf/rules/` | `.github/instructions/` |
| mcp | `.mcp.json` | `.mcp.json` | `.mcp.json` | — |

Rules installed by coding-aegis are prefixed `aegis--` to distinguish governance-managed files from project-owned files.

## Scope

Packages can be installed to:

- **Project** — governs a single repository
- **User** — applies across all repositories for the current user
- **Local** — applies to you in this repository only
